Going way back (three decades), the first earth-shattering confirmation of AQ was the Law of Thelema:
"Do what thou wilt shall be the whole of the Law" (AQ 777), echoing Crowley's title for his most prominent book of qabbalistic writings. ...

... This is the number of "And God said, Let there be light: And there was light." [Genesis 1:3]
It is evidently a number with magical associations, tied to the first spell. ...

... But, at least superficially, 777 is far less arithmetically important than 666 (number of the 36th Trigon, and Eighth Meta-Trigon). 
It is also has less (explicit or exoteric) biblical prominence, being found only once in Scripture, as the life-span of Lamech. ...

... “And all the days of Lamech were seven hundred seventy and seven years …” [Genesis 5:31] 
It's entirely missing (overtly) from the New Testament.
